gmx:name.gco:CharacterString: Feature catalog for United States Major Highways, 2000-2008

gmx:scope.gco:CharacterString: Express highways; Interstate highway system; Roads

gfc:definition.gco:CharacterString: The lines represent the major highways of the United States. These include interstates, U.S. highways, state highways, and major roads.
The name or route number of the highway.
The highway class (used for routing and connectivity).
A special class of highway to do very fast high level cross-country routing that also selects the through-route in complicated urban areas.
